The effect of a water-soluble vitamins on the activity of some enzymes in diabetes. Intramuscular injections of the vitamin complex containing: thiamine chloride (B1), riboflavin (B2), lipoic acid (N), calcium pantothenate (B5), pyridoxine hydrochloride (B6), folic acid (B9), ascorbic acid (C) can reduce the blood glucose level in serum of rats with alloxan diabetes, stabilize activity of some enzymes of energy metabolism, lactate dehydrogenase and pyruvate dehydrogenase complex. Vnutrimyshechnoe vvedenie vitaminnykh kompleksov, vkliuchaiushchikh tiamina khlorid (V1), riboflavin (V2), lipoevuiu kislotu (N), pantotenat kal'tsiia (V5), piridoksina gidrokhlorid (V6), folievuiu kislotu (V9), askorbinovuiu kislotu (S) pozvoliaet umen'shit' uroven' gliukozy v syvorotke krovi krys s alloksanovym diabetom, stabilizirovat' aktivnost' riada fermentov Ã©nergeticheskogo obmena, laktatdegidrogenazy i piruvatdegidrogenaznogo kompleksa.